(1. Observer Pattern) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 438 Tm
(- Board acts as the subject.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm
(- Board stores GameObserver listeners.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 402 Tm
(- Board.notifyObservers\(...\) broadcasts completed moves.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 384 Tm
(- MoveLogger, CheckDetector, and ChessGUI implement GameObserver.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 366 Tm
(- This separates move logging, check detection, and UI refresh work from board storage.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 348 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 50 330 Tm
(2. Factory Pattern) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 312 Tm
(- PieceFactory.create\(type, row, col, isWhite\) is the central piece-creation method.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm
(- GameManager.initBoard\(\) uses it to create the starting position.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 276 Tm
(- GameManager.promote\(...\) uses it to create promoted pieces.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 258 Tm
(- This avoids scattering direct constructor calls throughout the codebase.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 240 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 50 222 Tm
(3. Singleton Pattern) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 204 Tm
(- GameManager has a private constructor.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 186 Tm
(- GameManager stores a static instance.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 168 Tm
(- GameManager.getInstance\(\) returns one shared controller object.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 150 Tm
(- Main, ChessGUI, and BoardPanel all use that same shared state.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 132 Tm
() Tj
